39m═[0m[1m[38;5;51m═[0m[1m[38;5;45m═[0m[1m[38;5;82m═[0m[1m[38;5;118m═[0m[1m[38;5;226m═[0m[1m[38;5;220m═[0m[1m[38;5;214m═[0m[1m[38;5;208m═[0m[1m[38;5;202m═[0m[1m[38;5;196m═[0m[1m[38;5;207m═[0m[1m[38;5;201m═[0m[1m[38;5;147m═[0m[1m[38;5;111m═[0m[1m[38;5;75m═[0m[1m[38;5;39m═[0m
[1m[38;5;220mWhat is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mEach market object receives a point in a circular field: goodness on one axis, popularity on the other, hierarchy as a height-like layer above it.
[1m[38;5;118mWhy this is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mThe model must separate what is liked from what is good; otherwise a harmful but attractive object looks the same as a useful object.

[1m[38;5;207mAbbreviations used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;46mGV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mGoodness value: positive values mean social benefit, fewer harms, fairer side effects; negative values mean damage or exploitation.
  [1m[38;5;201mPV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mPopularity value: public demand, attraction, fashion, habit or approval; it is deliberately not identical to goodness.
  [1m[38;5;226mHV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mHierarchy value: structural rank; high values mean many lower actions, roles or consequences depend on the object.
  [1m[38;5;51mAD[0m[38;5;244m = [0mAxis direction: the angle created by goodness and popularity; it reveals the quadrant of the object.
  [1m[38;5;81mRW[0m[38;5;244m = [0mRadial width: distance from the neutral center; high values mean a very clear or polarizing position.
  [1m[38;5;214mMW[0m[38;5;244m = [0mMoral weight: compressed comparison signal from goodness, popularity, hierarchy and risk.
[1m[38;5;45mUnits used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;82mpts[0m[38;5;244m = [0mpoints on a normalized scale
  [1m[38;5;51mdeg[0m[38;5;244m = [0mangle degrees of the circular direction
  [1m[38;5;214mMCU[0m[38;5;244m = [0mmoral currency units
