[1m[38;5;220mWhat is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mSelected products are repeatedly re-scored. Institutions push goodness, population shifts popularity, and knowledge corrects both when measured consequences appear.
[1m[38;5;118mWhy this is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mA moral market layer is fragile if one actor can define truth alone. This step tests whether separated signals produce a more stable value vector.

[1m[38;5;207mAbbreviations used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;39mIS[0m[38;5;244m = [0mInstitutional signal: law, audit and public authority acting on harm, benefit and fairness.
  [1m[38;5;207mPS[0m[38;5;244m = [0mPopulation signal: collective desire, dislike, fashion, habit and public attention.
  [1m[38;5;118mKS[0m[38;5;244m = [0mKnowledge signal: measured consequences, research and evidence correcting both sides.
  [1m[38;5;46mGV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mGoodness value after signal pressure.
  [1m[38;5;201mPV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mPopularity value after signal pressure.
  [1m[38;5;82mDG[0m[38;5;244m = [0mDelta goodness: the change of goodness in the current step.
  [1m[38;5;213mDP[0m[38;5;244m = [0mDelta popularity: the change of popularity in the current step.
[1m[38;5;45mUnits used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;82mpts[0m[38;5;244m = [0mpoints on the value scale
