[1m[38;5;220mWhat is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mProducts are sold through demand, supply, tax or relief and moral weight. The price is still numeric, but it is embedded in a colored value context.
[1m[38;5;118mWhy this is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mA market price can hide exploitation, addiction or external costs. The simulation makes the hidden context visible before transactions are counted.

[1m[38;5;207mAbbreviations used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;220mRP[0m[38;5;244m = [0mReference price: end price after popularity, goodness, hierarchy and tax-or-relief pressure.
  [1m[38;5;75mDI[0m[38;5;244m = [0mDemand index: current pull of customers toward the product.
  [1m[38;5;159mSU[0m[38;5;244m = [0mSupply units: available product pieces in this step.
  [1m[38;5;203mTR[0m[38;5;244m = [0mTax-or-relief rate: positive means surcharge, negative means support.
  [1m[38;5;141mTX[0m[38;5;244m = [0mTransactions: simulated completed product exchanges.
  [1m[38;5;46mGV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mGoodness value used by the filter.
  [1m[38;5;201mPV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mPopularity value used by demand.
  [1m[38;5;214mMW[0m[38;5;244m = [0mMoral weight used as context, not as a bare price.
[1m[38;5;45mUnits used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;220mEUR[0m[38;5;244m = [0mconventional price reference
  [1m[38;5;207m%[0m[38;5;244m = [0mrate, index or share
  [1m[38;5;118mpc[0m[38;5;244m = [0mcounted product pieces
  [1m[38;5;208mtx[0m[38;5;244m = [0mcounted transactions
  [1m[38;5;214mMCU[0m[38;5;244m = [0mmoral currency units
