[1m[38;5;220mWhat is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mWorkers and employers are matched by productive ability, selfless contribution, fairness and moral weight. The employer does not monopolize judgment.
[1m[38;5;118mWhy this is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mClassic labor markets often overrate pay and underrate employer quality. This part tests a more symmetric market relation.

[1m[38;5;207mAbbreviations used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;111mWP[0m[38;5;244m = [0mWorker potential: skill, reliability and productive capacity of the worker.
  [1m[38;5;207mSE[0m[38;5;244m = [0mSelflessness: contribution beyond narrow private gain.
  [1m[38;5;118mFR[0m[38;5;244m = [0mFairness rate: employer-side fairness from wages, risk and goodness.
  [1m[38;5;51mMG[0m[38;5;244m = [0mMatch grade: quality of the worker-employer fit.
  [1m[38;5;221mWA[0m[38;5;244m = [0mWage adjustment: change in pay caused by match and fairness.
  [1m[38;5;214mMW[0m[38;5;244m = [0mMoral weight of worker and employer context.
[1m[38;5;45mUnits used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;82mpts[0m[38;5;244m = [0mpoints for skill, fairness and fit
  [1m[38;5;207m%[0m[38;5;244m = [0mrate or probability share
