[1m[38;5;220mWhat is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mCompany shares move by earnings, popularity, risk and moral weight. A high profit can still carry a warning color.
[1m[38;5;118mWhy this is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mCapital allocation is powerful. This step tests whether investors can see when return comes from helpful production or from damaging extraction.

[1m[38;5;207mAbbreviations used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;81mSV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mShare value: simulated share reference after value-vector pressure.
  [1m[38;5;118mER[0m[38;5;244m = [0mEarnings rate: current profit pressure translated into market movement.
  [1m[38;5;205mES[0m[38;5;244m = [0mEthical spread: moral premium or discount around the share.
  [1m[38;5;203mRS[0m[38;5;244m = [0mRisk shadow: risk and hidden-cost burden on the share.
  [1m[38;5;214mMW[0m[38;5;244m = [0mMoral weight of the company behind the share.
[1m[38;5;45mUnits used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;220mEUR[0m[38;5;244m = [0mshare price reference
  [1m[38;5;207m%[0m[38;5;244m = [0mrate, spread or burden
  [1m[38;5;214mMCU[0m[38;5;244m = [0mmoral currency units
