[1m[38;5;220mWhat is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mCountries receive exchange-like references from trust, risk, hierarchy and moral weight. The output shows a currency field rather than a single neutral number.
[1m[38;5;118mWhy this is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mIf currency reflects only liquidity, large harmful systems may look strong. This part tests a value-aware exchange layer.

[1m[38;5;207mAbbreviations used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;45mXR[0m[38;5;244m = [0mExchange rate: simulated rate against the shared moral currency reference.
  [1m[38;5;82mTC[0m[38;5;244m = [0mTrust correction: credibility gain or loss from goodness and stability.
  [1m[38;5;196mRR[0m[38;5;244m = [0mRisk reserve: extra buffer demanded for risk and harmful popularity.
  [1m[38;5;46mGV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mGoodness value of the country-level system.
  [1m[38;5;201mPV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mPopularity value of the country-level system.
  [1m[38;5;226mHV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mHierarchy value of the country-level system.
  [1m[38;5;214mMW[0m[38;5;244m = [0mMoral weight behind the exchange reference.
[1m[38;5;45mUnits used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;81mrate[0m[38;5;244m = [0mexchange-rate reference
  [1m[38;5;207m%[0m[38;5;244m = [0mcorrection, reserve or pressure
  [1m[38;5;82mpts[0m[38;5;244m = [0mpoints for value dimensions
  [1m[38;5;214mMCU[0m[38;5;244m = [0mmoral currency units
