[1m[38;5;220mWhat is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mRisks are priced, but premiums are modified by need, public usefulness and solidarity. Not every risk is treated as privately deserved.
[1m[38;5;118mWhy this is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mA value-aware market must distinguish between self-caused harmful risk and socially necessary exposure.

[1m[38;5;207mAbbreviations used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;203mRI[0m[38;5;244m = [0mRisk index: expected burden from accidents, uncertainty and external damage.
  [1m[38;5;45mSB[0m[38;5;244m = [0mSolidarity buffer: relief when need and useful purpose justify shared protection.
  [1m[38;5;220mPR[0m[38;5;244m = [0mPremium reference: simulated insurance premium after risk and solidarity.
  [1m[38;5;159mND[0m[38;5;244m = [0mNeed: urgency of protection for the insured case.
  [1m[38;5;214mMW[0m[38;5;244m = [0mMoral weight of the insured case.
[1m[38;5;45mUnits used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;220mEUR[0m[38;5;244m = [0mpremium reference
  [1m[38;5;207m%[0m[38;5;244m = [0mrisk or relief share
  [1m[38;5;82mpts[0m[38;5;244m = [0mneed and value points
  [1m[38;5;214mMCU[0m[38;5;244m = [0mmoral currency units
