[1m[38;5;220mWhat is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mWorkers, companies and products can rise or fall in hierarchy. Popularity alone is not enough if the moral signal is weak.
[1m[38;5;118mWhy this is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mThe original idea treats hierarchy as movable. This part tests promotion, demotion and unstable status.

[1m[38;5;207mAbbreviations used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;82mUP[0m[38;5;244m = [0mUpward chance: probability of reaching a higher responsibility layer.
  [1m[38;5;196mDN[0m[38;5;244m = [0mDownward pressure: probability of falling because of risk, harm or weak contribution.
  [1m[38;5;214mMT[0m[38;5;244m = [0mMovement trend: current productive direction of the object.
  [1m[38;5;46mGV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mGoodness value influencing stable ascent.
  [1m[38;5;201mPV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mPopularity value influencing fast ascent.
  [1m[38;5;226mHV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mHierarchy value before movement.
  [1m[38;5;214mMW[0m[38;5;244m = [0mMoral weight as a final interpretation layer.
[1m[38;5;45mUnits used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;207m%[0m[38;5;244m = [0mchance or pressure
  [1m[38;5;82mpts[0m[38;5;244m = [0mtrend and hierarchy points
  [1m[38;5;214mMCU[0m[38;5;244m = [0mmoral currency units
