[1m[38;5;220mWhat is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mA harmful but attractive product receives artificial popularity. Shielding mechanisms then try to slow the drift into the harmful-popular quadrant.
[1m[38;5;118mWhy this is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mThe model is dangerous if popularity can be manufactured cheaply. This part shows the race between manipulation and protection.

[1m[38;5;207mAbbreviations used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;201mMP[0m[38;5;244m = [0mManipulation pressure: artificial popularity from ads, data tricks, bots or habit loops.
  [1m[38;5;51mSP[0m[38;5;244m = [0mShield power: ability of transparency, audit and public learning to slow manipulation.
  [1m[38;5;46mGV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mGoodness value during the stress test.
  [1m[38;5;201mPV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mPopularity value during the stress test.
  [1m[38;5;51mAD[0m[38;5;244m = [0mAxis direction showing the rotation of the object in the field.
  [1m[38;5;214mMW[0m[38;5;244m = [0mMoral weight after manipulation and shielding pressure.
[1m[38;5;45mUnits used only in this part[0m
