[1m[38;5;220mWhat is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mA scarce resource is allocated not merely by purchasing power. Need, goodness, hierarchy, popularity and moral weight form a claim level.
[1m[38;5;118mWhy this is simulated[0m[38;5;246m — [0mThis tests the radical core of the idea: a currency-like system should reveal whom something is due to, without destroying minimum protection.

[1m[38;5;207mAbbreviations used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;220mCL[0m[38;5;244m = [0mClaim level: combined claim from need, value, hierarchy and public relevance.
  [1m[38;5;159mND[0m[38;5;244m = [0mNeed: urgency of the recipient or purpose.
  [1m[38;5;118mQU[0m[38;5;244m = [0mQuota: share of the scarce resource after minimum protection and claim weighting.
  [1m[38;5;46mGV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mGoodness value of the recipient or purpose.
  [1m[38;5;201mPV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mPopularity value; included weakly so popularity does not dominate.
  [1m[38;5;226mHV[0m[38;5;244m = [0mHierarchy value; higher if collapse would affect many others.
  [1m[38;5;214mMW[0m[38;5;244m = [0mMoral weight entering the claim calculation.
[1m[38;5;45mUnits used only in this part[0m
  [1m[38;5;118mpc[0m[38;5;244m = [0mpieces of the scarce resource
  [1m[38;5;82mpts[0m[38;5;244m = [0mneed and value points
  [1m[38;5;207m%[0m[38;5;244m = [0mallocation share
  [1m[38;5;214mMCU[0m[38;5;244m = [0mmoral currency units
